AD_COLUMN.NAME: Update Payment Monitor
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Update payment monitor information
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Update payment monitor information

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Total Paid
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Total amount paid.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Total amount paid.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Charge
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A cost or expense incurred during business activity.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Charge indicates a type of Charge (Handling, Shipping, Restocking)

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Print Discount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An option to have any discount printed on the invoice.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Discount Printed Checkbox indicates if the discount will be printed on the document.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Tax Date
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Tax Date
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Tax Date

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Document Action
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A means of changing the transaction status of the document.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: You find the current status in the Document Status field. The options are listed in a popup

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Copy from
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An addition of statements from pre-existing documents.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Copy lines (products) from another document of the same type.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Outstanding Amount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Outstanding Amount
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Outstanding Amount. Amount pending to be paid

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Summed Line Amount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The final sum of all line totals made to a specified document or transaction (not including taxes).
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Total amount displays the total of all lines in document currency.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Create Lines From
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An addition of statements from pre-existing documents.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: A process that allows the user to copy lines (products) from an existing document different from the one being copied into. For example, in case of entering a new Goods Shipment, the user can copy lines (products) from an existing Sales Order or Sales Invoice.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Self-Service
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Self-Service allows users to enter data or update their data. The flag indicates, that this record was entered or created via Self-Service or that the user can change it via the Self-Service functionality.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Self-Service allows users to enter data or update their data. The flag indicates, that this record was entered or created via Self-Service or that the user can change it via the Self-Service functionality.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: lineNo
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A line stating the position of this request in the document.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Indicates the unique line for a document. It will also control the display order of the lines within a document.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Withholdingamount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Withholding amount

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Cash VAT
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Cash VAT tax rate
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Cash VAT tax rate

AD_COLUMN.NAME: prName
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An item produced by a process.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Identifies an item which is either purchased or sold in this organization.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: User/Contact
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An acquaintance to reach for information related to the business partner.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The User identifies a unique user in the system. This could be an internal user or a business partner contact

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Generate To
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Generate To
AD_COLUMN.HELP: A button that creates documents

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Grand Total Amount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The final monetary amount (including taxes) charge listed in a document.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Grand Total displays the total amount including Tax and Freight in document currency

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Price List
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A catalog of selected items with prices defined generally or for a specific partner.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Price Lists are used to determine the pricing, margin and cost of items purchased or sold.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Accounting Date
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The date this transaction is recorded for in the general ledger.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The date this transaction is recorded on in the general ledger. This date also indicates which accounting period within the fiscal year this transaction will be part of.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Invoice
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A document listing products, quantities and prices, payment terms, etc.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Invoice ID uniquely identifies an Invoice Document.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Charge Amount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The amount of a cost or expense incurred during business activity.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Charge Amount indicates the amount for an additional charge.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Currency
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An accepted medium of monetary exchange that may vary across countries.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Indicates the currency to be used when processing this document.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Cost Center
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Division that adds to the cost of an organization
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Division that adds to the cost of an organization. Internal structure for cost allocation.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Form of Payment
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The method used for payment of this transaction.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Form of Payment indicates the method of payment used for this transaction (eg. cash, wire transfer, etc.)

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Sales Representative
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The person in charge of a document.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Indicates the sales representative responsible for the transaction that the document specifies . A valid sales representative is a business partner marked as an employee and a sales representative.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Creation Date
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The date that this record is completed.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Updated By
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: User who updated this records
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Updated By field indicates the user who updated this record.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Partner Address
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The location of the selected business partner.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Partner address indicates the location of a Business Partner

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Document Type
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A value defining what sequence and process setup are used to handle this document.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Document Type determines document sequence and processing rules

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Business Partner
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Anyone who takes part in daily business operations by acting as a customer, employee, etc.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: A Business Partner is anyone with whom you transact. This can include a customer, vendor, employee or any combination of these.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: 2nd Dimension
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A display of optional elements that are previously defined for this account combination.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The user defined element displays the optional elements that have been defined for this account combination.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Transaction Document
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The specific document type which should be used for the document.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Specifies document subtype (eg. POS Order, Return Material, etc.) that each document (such as Sales Invoice, Purchase Order, etc.). Various document subtypes usually differ on the consequences they have. You can convert document types (e.g. from Offer to Order). The conversion is then reflected in the current type.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Description
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A space to write additional related information.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: A description is limited to 255 characters.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Days Till Next Due
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Days Till Next Due
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Number of days left for the next due date

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Withholding
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Withholding
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Withholding indicates the type of withholding to be calculated.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Payment Complete
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A confirmation stating whether the request has been closed through a monetary transaction.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The document is paid for.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Due Amount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Due Amount
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Total amount due

AD_COLUMN.NAME: grossAmount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Gross Amount for a line
AD_COLUMN.HELP: This is the total amount against a line ( i.e product price * quantity + taxes )

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Order Reference
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A reference or document order number as listed in business partner application.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: This can be used to input a reference for this specific transaction. For example, a Purchase Order number can be input on a Sales Order for easier reference.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Price includes Tax
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Tax is included in the price
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Tax Included checkbox indicates if the prices include tax. This is also known as the gross price.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Sales Transaction
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An indication that a transfer of goods and money between business partners is occurring.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Sales Transaction checkbox indicates if this item is a Sales Transaction.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Project
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Identifier of a project defined within the Project & Service Management module.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Identifier of a project defined within the Project & Service Management module.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Returned
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Returned
AD_COLUMN.HELP: If it is checked means that the debt/payment has been returned by the bank.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Payment Terms
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The setup and timing defined to complete a specified payment.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Payment Terms identify the method and timing of payment for this transaction.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Sales Order
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A unique and often automatically generated identifier for a sales order.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Unique identifier and a reference to a Sales Order originating from the document sequence defined for this document type.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Client
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: operativeQuantity
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The number of a certain item involved in the transaction, according to the defined Operative UOM.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The number of a certain item involved in the transaction, according to the defined Operative UOM.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Document No.
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An often automatically generated identifier for all documents.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The document number is usually automatically generated by the system and determined by the document type of the document. If the document is not saved, the preliminary number is displayed in "<>". If the document type of your document has no automatic document sequence defined, the field will be empty when creating a new document. This is for documents which usually have an external number (like vendor invoice). If you leave the field empty, the system will generate a document number for you. The document sequence used for this fallback number is defined in the "Document Sequence" window with the name "DocumentNo_<TableName>", where TableName is the actual name of the table inside the database (e.g. C_Order).

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Activity
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A distinct activity defined and used in activity based management.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Activities indicate tasks that are performed and used to utilize Activity based Costing

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Payment Method
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: It is the method by which payment is expected to be made or received.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Organization
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Organizational entity within client
AD_COLUMN.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Process Now
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A request to process the respective document or task.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: When this field is set as 'Y' a process is being performed on this record.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Payment Priority
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Sets the priority of the payment plans generated when processing the invoice or order.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Sets the priority of the payment plans generated when processing the invoice or order. The distribution algorithm will be driven by this priority. The pending payments for order or payments will be displayed ordered by the payment priority first and then by the due date.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Last Calculated on Date
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Last Calculated On Date for payment monitor
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Last Calculated On Date for payment monitor

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Created By
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: User who created this records
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Created By field indicates the user who created this record.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Date printed
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Date the document was printed.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Indicates the Date that a document was printed.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Order Date
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The time listed on the order.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Indicates the Date an item was ordered.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Print
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A reference stating whether or not the document has been printed at any time in the past.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Printed checkbox indicates if this document or line will included when printing.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Updated
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The date that this record was last updated
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Updated field indicates the date that this record was updated.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Posted
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An accounting status button that indicates if the transaction has already been posted to the general ledger or not.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: An accounting status button that indicates if the transaction has already been posted to the general ledger or not. When doing the accounting manually this button can be used to post or unpost the transaction from the general ledger by hand.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: umName
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A non monetary unit of measure.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The UOM defines a unique non monetary unit of measure

AD_COLUMN.NAME: 1st Dimension
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A display of optional elements that are previously defined for this account combination.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The user defined element displays the optional elements that have been defined for this account combination.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Document Status
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The Document Status indicates the status of a document at this time.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Document Status indicates the status of a document at this time. To change the status of a document, use one of the buttons usually located at the bottom of the document window.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Active
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Trx Organization
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The organization which performs or initiates the transaction.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The organization which performs or initiates this transaction (for another organization). The owning Organization may not be the transaction organization in a service bureau environment, with centralized services, and inter-organization transactions.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: unitPrice
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Price inclusive of taxes
AD_COLUMN.HELP: This is the price that is provided when the price is inclusive of taxes.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: invoicedQuantity
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The total number of a product included in an invoice to a business partner.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Invoiced Quantity indicates the quantity of a product that have been invoiced.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Invoice Date
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The time listed on the invoice.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Date Invoice indicates the date printed on the invoice.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Processed
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A confirmation that the associated documents or requests are processed.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Processed checkbox indicates that a document has been processed.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: lineNetAmount
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The final amount of a specified line, based only on quantities and prices.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Indicates the line net amount based on the quantity and the actual price. Any additional charges or freight are not included.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Sales Campaign
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An advertising effort aimed at increasing sales.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Campaign defines a unique marketing program. Projects can be associated with a pre defined Marketing Campaign. You can then report based on a specific Campaign.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Asset
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: An item which is owned and exchangeable for cash.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Any item of economic value owned by the corporation, especially that which could be converted to cash.
